FBIS3-34205 "drnes025_g_94003" FBIS-NES-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 Sudan Armed Group Attacks Mosque in Omdurman 3 Attackers Reportedly Killed EA0502210394 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in Arabic 1900 GMT 5 Feb 94 EA0502210394 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Brigadier 'Abd-al-Rahim Muhammad Husayn, the interior minister, issued a statement a few moments ago about developments in the evil aggression by gunfire against worshipers in the mosque of the town Quarter One at al-Thawrah in Omdurman as well as later developments in the incident. He made it clear that the joint efforts of the interior minister, the people's Armed Forces, the general security and the citizens had made it possible to establish the identity, descriptions, and names of the criminals. He added that investigations had not ceased since the incident took place. [Words indistinct] in the three towns [Khartoum, Omdurman, and Khartoum north], clarifying that after the broadcasting of the statement on the identities of the criminals late this afternoon, the criminals moved with the intention of fleeing after they had been exposed, but the different security organizations were waiting for them. There was an exchange of gunfire as a result of which three of the criminals were killed. They are: 'Abd-al-Baqi Yusuf and Yasir Muhammad Ali from West Africa. The third was wounded. He is Muhammad Abdullah 'Abd-al-Rahman al-Khilayfi from Arab North Africa. He was taken to hospital. The minister of the interior said that documents had been discovered and confirmed the dimension of this conspiratorial [word indistinct] incident which our people and their peaceful traditions (?do not accept). His Excellency commended the vigilance of the citizens and their cooperation with the security organs which helped capture the criminals.
